(uniquement sysop)
syntaxe: HOLD [-u] <range>

Sets defined mail to HOLD (no S&F). You can release held mails with the
option "-u". You can list hold messages with DIR HOLD.

Note: This command is usally nonsens. Better use hold actions in "reject.bcm".
To release mails from held status, the option "-u" is a good choice. Mails
can also be released with "forward -h" command.

