 POP3 (internet) TTY password                a ttypw (uniquement sysop)
 SMTP (ampr.org) name                        a name
 SMTP (internet) TTY password                a ttypw (uniquement sysop)
 HTTP (ampr.org) name                        a name
 HTTP (internet) TTY password                a ttypw (uniquement sysop)

Command "PRIV" can be used if a file "<call>.bcm" or "priv.bcm" exists.
Sysop passwords must be setup in file "passwd.bcm".

When using an AX25-Password, normally HTTP/POP3/NNTP can't be used, because
there should be no security hole for call misusage. If AX25-Password contain
